# Design doc governance

## Source of truth

| Layer | Location | Who edits | Agent default |
|-------|----------|-----------|---------------|
| **Gameplay design** | `docs/design/卡牌游戏.md` | **User only** | Read-only |
| **Edit rules** | `docs/design/DESIGN_DOC_GOVERNANCE.md` | User | Read-only unless user asks |
| **AI / process docs** | `docs/ai/` | User + agent per workflow | Editable per workflow |
| **Implementation specs** | `docs/ai/Core/`, `Combat/`, `Data/`, etc. | User + agent when tasked | Editable when implementing |

`docs/design/` is **not** under `docs/ai/` — gameplay authority is separate from AI collaboration artifacts.

## Agent may read `卡牌游戏.md` when

- Session bootstrap or user asks about gameplay/rules.
- Implementing a user-scoped task (cite the section relied on).
- Drafting REQUIREMENTS or design discussion in chat or separate Draft files.

## Agent must NOT (default)

- Edit, rename, or delete `docs/design/卡牌游戏.md` without **explicit user request**.
- Treat chat paraphrases as approved design — confirm or wait for user to update the design doc.
- Silently resolve conflicts between design doc and code; ask the user.

## When user explicitly delegates design edits

Phrases like: 「帮我在卡牌游戏.md 里改…」「更新设计文档里的公式」.

Then:

1. Confirm **file** and **scope** (one section / one change).
2. Make **minimal** edits only in that scope.
3. Note in `docs/ai/PROGRESS_LOG.md` (path + brief summary).

## `docs/design/` vs `docs/ai/`

- **`docs/design/`** — gameplay (`卡牌游戏.md`), governance, future formal specs (REQUIREMENTS, GLOSSARY).
- **`docs/ai/`** — PROJECT_CONTEXT, ACTIVE_WORK, templates, implementation design under subdirs.
